20/12/2005
PARIS, France -- Serbian President Boris Tadic met on Monday (19 December) with French counterpart Jacques Chirac in Paris and says he was reassured of French support for Serbia's EU integration bid.
According to Tadic, the two presidents also agreed that the solution to the Kosovo issue must lead to peace and stability for the whole region.
In Belgrade meanwhile, Serbia-Montenegro and EU officials began the first round of technical negotiations on the Stabilisation and Association Agreement Tuesday.
Liberalising trade with the EU will be the focus of discussions.
In other news, Montenegrin President Filip Vujanovic has scheduled an extraordinary parliamentary session on 7 February, dedicated to the independence referendum.
He said that the vote would likely take place before April.
(RTS, Beta - 19/12/05)
